solutions.content:
Calculate frequency of each element in nums ( map -1000 to index 1 )
While traversing freq array we can encounter 3 cases. Calculate freq[i] > freq[i-1] ( say d )
(a) d > 0 : d number of intervals start from this point. Push back into deque.
(b) d < 0 : d number of intervals expire at i-1. Pop front from deque and check size > 3.
(c) d = 0 : do nothing.
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool isPossible(vector<int>& nums) {
        deque<int> dq;
        vector<int> freq(2003);
        for( int i : nums ) 
            freq[i+1001]++;

        for( int i = 1; i < freq.size(); i++ ){
            int d = freq[i]-freq[i-1];
            while( d > 0 ){
                dq.push_back(i);
                d--;
            }
            while( d < 0 ){
                if(i-dq.front()<3)
                    return false;
                dq.pop_front();
                d++;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
};
```

