solutions.content:
Just maintain three variables and traverse the array. 
1. len1cnt : count of subsequences of length 1 alive till now.
2. len2cnt : count of subsequences of length 2 alive till now.
3. len3plusCnt : count of subsequences of length 3 or more alive till now.

For every new element, we find frequency(freq) of it by looking ahead.
update those three variables greedily and skip the iteration by freq positions.
Here greedily means, give preferences to len1cnt & len2cnt variable while consuming the freq of the current element. Because if we were not able to extend them, then it will immediate return false i.e. no split is possible.
```
bool isPossible(vector<int>& nums) {
        int len1cnt=0,len2cnt=0,len3plusCnt=0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();){
            int j=i+1;
            while(j<nums.size() && nums[j]==nums[i]) ++j;
            int freq=j-i;
            if(len1cnt+len2cnt>freq)
                return false;
            freq -= len1cnt+len2cnt;
            if(freq<=len3plusCnt){
                len3plusCnt = freq + len2cnt;
                len2cnt = len1cnt;
                len1cnt =0;
            }else{
                freq-=len3plusCnt;
                len3plusCnt += len2cnt;
                len2cnt=len1cnt;
                len1cnt=freq;
            }
            if(j<nums.size() && nums[i]+1 != nums[j]){
                if(len1cnt || len2cnt) return false;
                len1cnt=0,len2cnt=0,len3plusCnt=0;
            }
            i=j;
        }
        if(len1cnt || len2cnt) return false;
        return true;
		}
```

