This solution is not fast but intuitive. I think it is acceptable during the interview.
```
public boolean isPossible(int[] nums) {
        Map<Integer, Integer> freq = new HashMap<>();
        for (int num : nums) {
            freq.put(num, freq.getOrDefault(num, 0) + 1);
        }

        for (int num : nums) {
            if (!freq.containsKey(num)) {
                continue;
            }
            int minOccur = 1;
            int tmp = num;
            while (freq.containsKey(tmp) && freq.get(tmp) >= minOccur) {
                minOccur = Math.max(minOccur, freq.get(tmp));
                freq.put(tmp, freq.get(tmp) - 1);
                if (freq.get(tmp) == 0) {
                    freq.remove(tmp);
                }
                tmp++;
            }
            if (tmp - num < 3) return false;
        }
        return freq.isEmpty();
    }
```

