Then i looked at the example and try to see what is happening. Till this point i have no idea how to do in a better way.
I read the problem statement again, noted two important keywords - **Sorted** and **consecutive**. 
Then i realised problem will be very easy if it doesnt have duplicates.
**Main Focus - Some decisions needs to be taken when duplicates are found.**
Still i cant figure what decision i can take when duplicates are found. So i decided to write the example on copy and see the pattern. Something i noticed . 
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/2ff4ac9b-28a2-47df-8204-5d8ad21e1ca1_1595189364.5891304.png)
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/a1cd315e-71ac-4a56-831f-83cf573974a4_1595189366.5415604.png)
