**Algorithm:**
1. Created two HashMap/ Unordered Map to store frequencies of each element and number of consecutive subsequence that ends at element value.
2. Loaded frequencies into count map.
3. Do the following: 
	a. If frequency of element is 0, continue (means number has already been used by previous subsequence)
	b. else decrease the frequency by 1.
	c. If  end map previous element frequency is greater than 0, decrease the previous value frequency and increase the current value frequency by 1
	d. else if next 2 element has frequency greater than 0, decrease its frequency by 1 and increment end map frequency by 1.
	e. else it is not possible to form subsequence, return false
4. If all cases run, return true means it is possible to form subsequence.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Auxiliary Space: O(n)

Here's code:

