solutions.content:
In essence, we are using the minheap to keep track of the valid and relevant vectors that we are constructing
If we cannot add onto or create a valid increasing vector of size three, then it is not possible to split the array.

Algorithm:
* First, we map numbers to their frequencies so we can confidently construct valid vectors of size three .
* Then, we go through all the numbers
	* First we eliminate any vectors that aren't relevant anymore (have back < curr-1 means that we can never add on to those subsequences)
	* Then, we check if there is already a valid array we can add to-- if so, then add it on to the array
	* Otherwise, attempt to construct a valid three array by checking the frequencies of curr +1 and curr + 2
	*  If we cannot do either of those aactions, we fail to split the array into consecutive subarrays

Another potential minheap solution involves mapping a minheap to each number, prioritizing "adding" to vectors of smallest size (which we can just keep track of size)

```
struct custom {
  bool operator()(const vector<int>& lhs, const vector<int>& rhs) {
	  return lhs.back() > rhs.back();
  }  
};
bool isPossible(vector<int>& nums) {
	map<int, int> freq;
	for(int i = 0; i < nums.size(); ++i)
		freq[nums[i]]++;

	priority_queue<vector<int>, vector<vector<int> >, custom> prio;
	for(auto it = freq.begin(); it != freq.end(); ++it) {
		int curr = it->first;

		while(it->second > 0) {
			while(!prio.empty() && prio.top().back() < curr - 1) //get potential valid 3+ vectors
				prio.pop();

			if(!prio.empty() && prio.top().back() == curr - 1) {
				//add it to a valid 3+ vector
				vector<int> copy = prio.top();
				prio.pop();
				copy.push_back(curr);
				prio.push(copy);
			} else if (freq[curr + 1] > 0 && freq[curr + 2] > 0) { //can create valid 3+ vector
				vector<int> validThree; //construct the valid vector
				validThree.push_back(curr);
				validThree.push_back(curr+1);
				validThree.push_back(curr+2);
				prio.push(validThree);
				//used the values-- subtract from freq map
				freq[curr+1]--;
				freq[curr+2]--;
			} else { //no valid operations available-- return false
				return false;
			}
			it->second--;
		}
	}
	return true;
}
```

