**For each word, keep going back through all the lists and see if you can add to one of them. If you can't, only then create a new list and add to it.**

This isn't the fastest solution, but hopefully it's a fairly easy one to understand.

Keep trying to add to the current list, and only go back if necessary.

Then, at the end, check if you have any lists which have a size < 3.
This check can probably be incorporated earlier, but I found it easier to reaason about by having another pass through the lists.

